{{Infobox scientist | name = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | image_size = | birth_date = {{birth date |1935|01|17}} | birth_place = [[Bangkok, Thailand]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.encyclopedia.com/science/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/gotschlich-emil-claus-1935|title=Gotschlich, Emil Claus (1935- ) - Dictionary definition of Gotschlich, Emil Claus (1935- ) {{!}} Encyclopedia.com: FREE online dictionary|website=www.encyclopedia.com|language=en|access-date=2017-04-16}}</ref> | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | citizenship = American | nationality = German | fields = | workplaces = {{plainlist| * [[Rockefeller University]] * }} | education = | alma_mater = {{plainlist| * [[New York University]] * }} | known_for = | awards = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> }} '''Emil Claus Gotschlich''' is a professor emeritus at the [[Rockefeller University]]. He is best known for his development of the first meningitis vaccine in 1970.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laskerfoundation.org/awards/show/vaccines-against-pneumonia-and-meningitis/|title=Vaccines against pneumonia and meningitis {{!}} The Lasker Foundation|last=Foundation|first=Lasker|website=The Lasker Foundation|language=en|access-date=2017-04-16}}</ref>
Gotschlich received his M.D. from the [[New York University School of Medicine]] in 1959. He interned at Bellevue Hospital in New York before joining The Rockefeller University's Laboratory of Bacteriology and Immunology in 1960. He was promoted to professor and senior physician at The Rockefeller University Hospital in 1978. From 1996 to 2005 he served as the hospital's vice president for medical sciences. He is a member of the National Academy of Sciences and its Institute of Medicine. He was the recipient of the 1978 [[Albert Lasker Clinical Medical Research Award]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rockefeller.edu/about/awards/lasker/egotschlich|title=The Rockefeller University » Awards & Honors|website=www.rockefeller.edu|language=en|access-date=2017-04-16}}</ref> He was the recipient of the 2008 Dart/NYU Biotechnology Achievement Award.<ref>https://www.rockefeller.edu/news/4831-cori-bargmann-honored-with-dartnyu-biotechnology-achievement-award</ref>
