{{Infobox lake | name = Lake Doxa | image = Lake Doxa 3.JPG | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = West [[Feneos]], [[Corinthia|Korinthia]] | coords = {{coord|37|55|45|N|22|17|11|E|region:GR-23_type:waterbody_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} | lake_type = Reservoir | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = Greece | length = {{convert|1.5|km|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|300|to|1000|m|abbr=on}} | area = about {{convert|5|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = {{convert|30|to|40|m|abbr=on}} | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|900|m|abbr=on}} | islands = | cities = }}
'''Lake Doxa''' ({{lang-el|Λίμνη Δόξα}} ''Limni Doxa'') is an [[reservoir|artificial lake]] in western [[Corinthia]], [[Greece]]. It is situated at an elevation of 900 m, in the municipal unit [[Feneos]], near the village [[Archaia Feneos]]. Construction was completed in the late 1990s. It is fed and drained by the small river ''Doxa'' (''Δόξα''), which empties into the plain of Feneos. In the heart of the lake on a small peninsula features a small church of [[Agios Fanourios]]. The [[Saint George Monastery in Feneos]] was relocated to higher ground, north of the lake. The lake is surrounded by pine forests.
